The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Unbeaten 129 by Mongia

London: Dinesh Mongia hit a magnificent unbeaten 129 to guide Leicestershire to 315 for 9 declared in the first innings of their three-day match against Pakistan Saturday. 

Put in to bat, the hosts lost three wickets for 73 before Mongia and John Sadler (92) bailed them out with a 147-run partnership for the fourth wicket. Mongia hit 18 boundaries during his knock which came off 234 balls. At stumps, Pakistan were 14 for no loss. 

